WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.177 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.177 --> 00:00:14.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: Hello, and welcome.

00:00:14.510 --> 00:00:15.926 align:middle line:90%
I'm Lisa Garr.

00:00:15.926 --> 00:00:17.050 align:middle line:90%
So let me ask you question.

00:00:17.050 --> 00:00:19.250 align:middle line:84%
Would you like to put
more of your focus

00:00:19.250 --> 00:00:20.920 align:middle line:90%
on living a committed life?

00:00:20.920 --> 00:00:22.260 align:middle line:10%
Now, what does that mean?

00:00:22.260 --> 00:00:26.170 align:middle line:10%
Do issues like sustainability
and poverty and world hunger

00:00:26.170 --> 00:00:28.420 align:middle line:10%
seem like things that are
outside of your reach, that

00:00:28.420 --> 00:00:30.110 align:middle line:10%
are outside of your grasp?

00:00:30.110 --> 00:00:32.110 align:middle line:10%
Would you like to
know how you, how

00:00:32.110 --> 00:00:35.120 align:middle line:10%
one person can
make a difference?

00:00:35.120 --> 00:00:38.570 align:middle line:84%
Joining me is someone who
really is making a difference.

00:00:38.570 --> 00:00:41.980 align:middle line:84%
Global activist and co-founder
of The Pachamama Alliance,

00:00:41.980 --> 00:00:43.330 align:middle line:90%
Lynne Twist.

00:00:43.330 --> 00:00:45.227 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much
for being with us.

00:00:45.227 --> 00:00:47.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LYNNE TWIST: It's my
pleasure, my delight.

00:00:47.060 --> 00:00:48.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's our honor, truly.

00:00:48.690 --> 00:00:49.560 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Thank you.

00:00:49.560 --> 00:00:55.257 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what inspires you to
make a difference in humanity?

00:00:55.257 --> 00:00:56.840 align:middle line:84%
Did you just wake
up one day-- I mean,

00:00:56.840 --> 00:01:00.140 align:middle line:84%
this has to be the root
of who you really are.

00:01:00.140 --> 00:01:02.580 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well, I think it's
the root of who everybody is.

00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:05.300 align:middle line:10%
I don't think I'm
unique in that way.

00:01:05.300 --> 00:01:09.840 align:middle line:10%
I think it lives like a burning
yearning for every human being.

00:01:09.840 --> 00:01:12.374 align:middle line:10%
And if you just remember
when you were a child

00:01:12.374 --> 00:01:14.415 align:middle line:10%
and you found out that
other children were hungry

00:01:14.415 --> 00:01:16.530 align:middle line:10%
or you found out
that there was war,

00:01:16.530 --> 00:01:18.540 align:middle line:10%
you wanted to do
something about it.

00:01:18.540 --> 00:01:21.699 align:middle line:84%
Every little child does unless
they're in those circumstances,

00:01:21.699 --> 00:01:23.740 align:middle line:84%
and even then they want
to do something about it.

00:01:23.740 --> 00:01:26.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But people get
disconnected from it

00:01:26.150 --> 00:01:29.870 align:middle line:84%
by feeling that it's
out of reach, that it's

00:01:29.870 --> 00:01:33.417 align:middle line:84%
too daunting, that they can't do
anything just being one person.

00:01:33.417 --> 00:01:34.250 align:middle line:90%
Have you heard that?

00:01:34.250 --> 00:01:36.520 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: I've heard
that a million times

00:01:36.520 --> 00:01:37.550 align:middle line:90%
if I've heard it once.

00:01:37.550 --> 00:01:42.640 align:middle line:84%
And I think what stops us is
this kind of very uniquely

00:01:42.640 --> 00:01:45.670 align:middle line:84%
human conversation that we
can't make a difference,

00:01:45.670 --> 00:01:49.070 align:middle line:84%
that we don't matter, that
our lives are too small.

00:01:49.070 --> 00:01:50.450 align:middle line:84%
But when you think
about history,

00:01:50.450 --> 00:01:53.130 align:middle line:84%
when you think about
any monumental change

00:01:53.130 --> 00:01:56.610 align:middle line:84%
or transformation in history,
it was caused, it was fomented,

00:01:56.610 --> 00:01:59.460 align:middle line:84%
it was inspired by a
regular human being

00:01:59.460 --> 00:02:01.710 align:middle line:90%
who took an extraordinary stand.

00:02:01.710 --> 00:02:04.820 align:middle line:84%
And that's available to
everybody alive today.

00:02:04.820 --> 00:02:07.650 align:middle line:84%
And there's so many ways
to live your life in a way

00:02:07.650 --> 00:02:09.970 align:middle line:84%
that you're fulfilled
and you know

00:02:09.970 --> 00:02:11.100 align:middle line:90%
that your life has meaning.

00:02:11.100 --> 00:02:12.450 align:middle line:84%
And it's really from
getting involved

00:02:12.450 --> 00:02:14.074 align:middle line:84%
in something that
makes your heart sing

00:02:14.074 --> 00:02:16.160 align:middle line:84%
and that's bigger than
your life starring you.

00:02:16.160 --> 00:02:18.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Who are
some of your idols

00:02:18.030 --> 00:02:23.000 align:middle line:84%
that really made a difference
in history, that inspired you?

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:25.360 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well, I
think all of us were

00:02:25.360 --> 00:02:27.420 align:middle line:90%
inspired by Mahatma Gandhi.

00:02:27.420 --> 00:02:30.196 align:middle line:84%
I've been lucky enough to
live and work in India for,

00:02:30.196 --> 00:02:31.320 align:middle line:90%
off and on, for many years.

00:02:31.320 --> 00:02:32.950 align:middle line:84%
I never lived
there, but I worked

00:02:32.950 --> 00:02:36.190 align:middle line:84%
there are over 18 years
for the Hunger Project.

00:02:36.190 --> 00:02:41.060 align:middle line:84%
And Gandhi's legacy is
so huge for everybody

00:02:41.060 --> 00:02:43.500 align:middle line:90%
in India but all over the world.

00:02:43.500 --> 00:02:47.540 align:middle line:84%
His phrases, "my life is
my message," "be the change

00:02:47.540 --> 00:02:50.200 align:middle line:84%
you wish to make in the
world," that's Gandhi.

00:02:50.200 --> 00:02:52.430 align:middle line:84%
He was an iconic of
making a difference.

00:02:52.430 --> 00:02:53.980 align:middle line:84%
A little individual,
little brown man

00:02:53.980 --> 00:02:55.970 align:middle line:84%
who really changed
the course of history.

00:02:55.970 --> 00:02:57.800 align:middle line:90%
Martin Luther King, of course.

00:02:57.800 --> 00:03:00.590 align:middle line:84%
People who are alive
today like Jane Goodall,

00:03:00.590 --> 00:03:04.470 align:middle line:84%
people like Marian Wright
Edelman, Nelson Mandela,

00:03:04.470 --> 00:03:07.860 align:middle line:84%
Desmond Tutu, the Nobel
women laureates are--

00:03:07.860 --> 00:03:09.910 align:middle line:84%
I'm privileged to
work with the Nobel's.

00:03:09.910 --> 00:03:12.000 align:middle line:84%
And I have the great
honor of knowing

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:14.860 align:middle line:84%
Jody Williams and
Rigoberta Menchu Tum.

00:03:14.860 --> 00:03:19.850 align:middle line:84%
And I find people who are in
that category of-- we kind of

00:03:19.850 --> 00:03:20.510 align:middle line:90%
revere them.

00:03:20.510 --> 00:03:21.660 align:middle line:84%
When you actually
get to know them,

00:03:21.660 --> 00:03:24.200 align:middle line:84%
it's just like talking to you,
it's just like talking to me.

00:03:24.200 --> 00:03:26.170 align:middle line:84%
They're just people
who had the-- they're

00:03:26.170 --> 00:03:29.160 align:middle line:84%
ordinary people, really
ordinary people, who

00:03:29.160 --> 00:03:32.940 align:middle line:84%
made an extraordinary choice
and extraordinary commitment.

00:03:32.940 --> 00:03:35.310 align:middle line:84%
And it generates an
extraordinary life.

00:03:35.310 --> 00:03:36.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So is that
the defining moment?

00:03:36.940 --> 00:03:39.100 align:middle line:84%
There's something
that changes a person

00:03:39.100 --> 00:03:40.870 align:middle line:84%
from wanting to
make a difference

00:03:40.870 --> 00:03:42.470 align:middle line:84%
and actually making
a difference.

00:03:42.470 --> 00:03:45.690 align:middle line:84%
Where do you think that fine
line or that changing moment

00:03:45.690 --> 00:03:46.660 align:middle line:90%
occurs?

00:03:46.660 --> 00:03:47.160 align:middle line:90%
In a person.

00:03:47.160 --> 00:03:50.850 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well, there's-- that's
such a good question and I wish

00:03:50.850 --> 00:03:53.230 align:middle line:84%
I could give a formula, but
I don't think there is one.

00:03:53.230 --> 00:03:56.550 align:middle line:84%
I think part of
it, I know for me,

00:03:56.550 --> 00:04:00.630 align:middle line:84%
was paying attention
to the openings

00:04:00.630 --> 00:04:05.130 align:middle line:84%
and pathways that life presents
you to make a difference.

00:04:05.130 --> 00:04:09.120 align:middle line:84%
And not turning away from them
or not being afraid of them.

00:04:09.120 --> 00:04:13.200 align:middle line:84%
It's in the way we listen to
what the universe brings to us.

00:04:13.200 --> 00:04:15.480 align:middle line:84%
It's in the way we
think about who we are

00:04:15.480 --> 00:04:18.160 align:middle line:84%
and how we kind of
show up for ourselves.

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:21.450 align:middle line:84%
And I was lucky,
very, very lucky,

00:04:21.450 --> 00:04:24.780 align:middle line:84%
to meet some extraordinary
people in my lifetime,

00:04:24.780 --> 00:04:29.450 align:middle line:84%
that I was able to see if I
could just be a little bit more

00:04:29.450 --> 00:04:30.720 align:middle line:90%
like them.

00:04:30.720 --> 00:04:33.140 align:middle line:84%
I ended up being
more like myself.

00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:38.570 align:middle line:84%
And so mentors and role models
are really powerful for people.

00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:41.850 align:middle line:84%
And especially if they're people
who kind of bring you back

00:04:41.850 --> 00:04:43.790 align:middle line:84%
to the power of
your own commitment,

00:04:43.790 --> 00:04:46.680 align:middle line:84%
your own life story,
your own capacities,

00:04:46.680 --> 00:04:48.956 align:middle line:84%
your own qualities of
love and commitment.

00:04:48.956 --> 00:04:50.830 align:middle line:84%
But I think it's a
function of love, frankly.

00:04:50.830 --> 00:04:53.110 align:middle line:84%
I think everything's
a function of love.

00:04:53.110 --> 00:04:56.420 align:middle line:84%
If you're willing to let
yourself love the world,

00:04:56.420 --> 00:04:59.490 align:middle line:84%
love other people,
love being alive,

00:04:59.490 --> 00:05:02.230 align:middle line:84%
all kinds of miraculous
things show up in your path

00:05:02.230 --> 00:05:04.390 align:middle line:84%
and you have the
opportunity to step into it.

00:05:04.390 --> 00:05:06.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So not seeing
yourself as separate

00:05:06.140 --> 00:05:10.740 align:middle line:84%
or as us versus them or as I'm
afraid that that could be me

00:05:10.740 --> 00:05:12.990 align:middle line:84%
so I don't want to talk
to that homeless person.

00:05:12.990 --> 00:05:17.267 align:middle line:84%
That concept, turning
that into love and--

00:05:17.267 --> 00:05:17.850 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yeah.

00:05:17.850 --> 00:05:18.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --and sharing.

00:05:18.820 --> 00:05:19.361 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yes.

00:05:19.361 --> 00:05:24.100 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the word compassion
really means with passion.

00:05:24.100 --> 00:05:26.560 align:middle line:84%
So I remember I had
a little experiment

00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:29.120 align:middle line:84%
I did for myself when the
homeless issue started

00:05:29.120 --> 00:05:30.760 align:middle line:84%
to really enter into
my consciousness.

00:05:30.760 --> 00:05:32.520 align:middle line:90%
In a way I was irritated.

00:05:32.520 --> 00:05:34.520 align:middle line:84%
I noticed I was irritated
by homeless people.

00:05:34.520 --> 00:05:38.490 align:middle line:84%
I was-- I didn't want
them to talk to me.

00:05:38.490 --> 00:05:42.645 align:middle line:84%
They were kind of in my way and
they were kind of intrusive.

00:05:42.645 --> 00:05:47.790 align:middle line:84%
I did a practice for Lent--
I was raised a Catholic,

00:05:47.790 --> 00:05:49.910 align:middle line:84%
I don't really practice
Catholicism any longer--

00:05:49.910 --> 00:05:53.050 align:middle line:84%
but Lent came and I kind of
thought, oh, I should do Lent.

00:05:53.050 --> 00:05:55.000 align:middle line:84%
Because this wonderful
teacher mine,

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:57.500 align:middle line:84%
Brother David Steindl-Rast,
an Austrian monk,

00:05:57.500 --> 00:06:00.100 align:middle line:84%
had just been staying
at my home and we'd

00:06:00.100 --> 00:06:01.180 align:middle line:90%
done some work together.

00:06:01.180 --> 00:06:05.150 align:middle line:84%
And he took me to
Ash Wednesday mass,

00:06:05.150 --> 00:06:08.000 align:middle line:84%
which I hadn't gone to
since I was like two,

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:10.210 align:middle line:84%
and I had this ash
thing on my forehead.

00:06:10.210 --> 00:06:11.764 align:middle line:90%
And then he left that day.

00:06:11.764 --> 00:06:13.180 align:middle line:84%
And I remember
that day I decided,

00:06:13.180 --> 00:06:14.471 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do Lent this year.

00:06:14.471 --> 00:06:17.710 align:middle line:84%
And so for 40 days I did
a whole group of practices

00:06:17.710 --> 00:06:21.610 align:middle line:84%
but one of them was that every
homeless person in my path,

00:06:21.610 --> 00:06:25.070 align:middle line:84%
I was going to talk to, I was
going to physically touch,

00:06:25.070 --> 00:06:27.330 align:middle line:84%
and I was going to contribute
to, not necessarily

00:06:27.330 --> 00:06:32.490 align:middle line:84%
financially, but actually have
them feel seen, respected,

00:06:32.490 --> 00:06:34.610 align:middle line:84%
and give them a sense
of their own dignity.

00:06:34.610 --> 00:06:36.570 align:middle line:90%
And I did it for 40 days.

00:06:36.570 --> 00:06:39.130 align:middle line:84%
And I can tell you, if you
ever do something like that,

00:06:39.130 --> 00:06:43.830 align:middle line:84%
it changes your life forever
about people you're afraid of,

00:06:43.830 --> 00:06:47.940 align:middle line:84%
people you think are
untouchable or unpresentable

00:06:47.940 --> 00:06:51.620 align:middle line:84%
or will somehow be
dangerous to you.

00:06:51.620 --> 00:06:53.530 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it shifted everything.

00:06:53.530 --> 00:06:57.250 align:middle line:84%
So I do think there is practices
we can do that kind of open up

00:06:57.250 --> 00:07:01.490 align:middle line:84%
our heart, that close down
that judgemental little voice

00:07:01.490 --> 00:07:02.450 align:middle line:90%
in our head.

00:07:02.450 --> 00:07:04.600 align:middle line:84%
And when you do something
like that, what happens

00:07:04.600 --> 00:07:06.870 align:middle line:90%
is you get transformed.

00:07:06.870 --> 00:07:09.350 align:middle line:84%
You start realizing
your own power

00:07:09.350 --> 00:07:11.870 align:middle line:84%
and the power of your
capacity to love.

00:07:11.870 --> 00:07:14.850 align:middle line:84%
And everything really
good in the world

00:07:14.850 --> 00:07:16.640 align:middle line:84%
really comes from
there, I think.

00:07:16.640 --> 00:07:19.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it changed and
shifted who you were being

00:07:19.080 --> 00:07:20.980 align:middle line:90%
and your thoughts around that.

00:07:20.980 --> 00:07:21.480 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:07:21.480 --> 00:07:22.980 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: And that's not
why I did it but I--

00:07:22.980 --> 00:07:23.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:07:23.190 --> 00:07:24.150 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: --ended
up making it-- I

00:07:24.150 --> 00:07:26.000 align:middle line:84%
think I made a big difference
with all these people too.

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:26.380 align:middle line:90%
I hope.

00:07:26.380 --> 00:07:26.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:26.880 align:middle line:90%
I'm sure.

00:07:26.880 --> 00:07:28.380 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: But certainly
what happened

00:07:28.380 --> 00:07:31.550 align:middle line:84%
for me was, I'd call
it a transformation.

00:07:31.550 --> 00:07:34.350 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So now fast forward to
what I had mentioned earlier.

00:07:34.350 --> 00:07:38.090 align:middle line:84%
You are the co-founder of
The Pachamama Alliance.

00:07:38.090 --> 00:07:39.459 align:middle line:90%
Which is enormous.

00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:41.500 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to talk
a lot about that, but how

00:07:41.500 --> 00:07:44.110 align:middle line:84%
did you get to that
place where you

00:07:44.110 --> 00:07:47.385 align:middle line:90%
co-founded an entire movement?

00:07:47.385 --> 00:07:48.010 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Well--

00:07:48.010 --> 00:07:49.815 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a big step.

00:07:49.815 --> 00:07:52.190 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: I just want to say,
it wasn't like I woke up one

00:07:52.190 --> 00:07:54.357 align:middle line:84%
morning and said, oh,
let's co-found a movement--

00:07:54.357 --> 00:07:54.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:07:54.940 --> 00:07:55.439 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:07:55.439 --> 00:07:57.520 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: --with
my husband, Bill.

00:07:57.520 --> 00:08:00.340 align:middle line:10%
It's really very similar
to what I'm describing.

00:08:00.340 --> 00:08:03.310 align:middle line:10%
We-- I was very involved
in-- and actually

00:08:03.310 --> 00:08:05.040 align:middle line:10%
one of the key
leaders-- of something

00:08:05.040 --> 00:08:06.410 align:middle line:10%
called the Hunger Project.

00:08:06.410 --> 00:08:08.880 align:middle line:10%
And I was working
all over the world

00:08:08.880 --> 00:08:12.770 align:middle line:10%
in India, Bangladesh,
sub-Saharan Africa,

00:08:12.770 --> 00:08:16.680 align:middle line:10%
places like Nepal, Sri Lanka,
Ethiopia, Angola, Namibia.

00:08:16.680 --> 00:08:19.380 align:middle line:10%
I was responsible for
operations in 47 countries.

00:08:19.380 --> 00:08:23.450 align:middle line:84%
I was very, very, very deeply
and profoundly committed

00:08:23.450 --> 00:08:24.550 align:middle line:90%
to ending world hunger.

00:08:24.550 --> 00:08:27.640 align:middle line:84%
And I was deeply
engaged in doing so.

00:08:27.640 --> 00:08:29.566 align:middle line:84%
And I had three
children and I had--

00:08:29.566 --> 00:08:30.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And you were a mom.

00:08:30.690 --> 00:08:33.380 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: I was a mom and I had
a husband who was in business

00:08:33.380 --> 00:08:37.210 align:middle line:84%
and kind of needed me to be
at his side from time to time.

00:08:37.210 --> 00:08:41.165 align:middle line:84%
So it was-- already I was
stretched to the absolute max

00:08:41.165 --> 00:08:42.395 align:middle line:90%
as most women know.

00:08:42.395 --> 00:08:43.770 align:middle line:84%
This is kind of
the way women are

00:08:43.770 --> 00:08:45.186 align:middle line:84%
these days,
particularly women who

00:08:45.186 --> 00:08:48.780 align:middle line:84%
have professional commitments
or philanthropic commitments

00:08:48.780 --> 00:08:49.401 align:middle line:90%
and kids.

00:08:49.401 --> 00:08:49.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:08:49.900 --> 00:08:52.430 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: So I did not
have one free iota, not

00:08:52.430 --> 00:08:57.460 align:middle line:84%
one free psychic minutia
space for anything more.

00:08:57.460 --> 00:09:00.740 align:middle line:84%
Yet, at the same time, while
I was really deeply devoted

00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:05.000 align:middle line:84%
to my work in sub-Saharan
Africa, India and Bangladesh,

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:10.110 align:middle line:84%
I got a very powerful
invitation to help a friend out

00:09:10.110 --> 00:09:12.680 align:middle line:84%
in-- who was running an
organization in Guatemala

00:09:12.680 --> 00:09:14.750 align:middle line:84%
with my colleague
John Perkins who

00:09:14.750 --> 00:09:18.380 align:middle line:84%
is a very well known
bestselling author

00:09:18.380 --> 00:09:20.729 align:middle line:84%
and has also been
trained as a shaman,

00:09:20.729 --> 00:09:22.270 align:middle line:84%
was in the Peace
Corps for many years

00:09:22.270 --> 00:09:24.210 align:middle line:90%
in Ecuador and the Amazon.

00:09:24.210 --> 00:09:27.660 align:middle line:84%
And he and I ended
up in Guatemala

00:09:27.660 --> 00:09:31.210 align:middle line:84%
with a whole lot of
things that preceded that,

00:09:31.210 --> 00:09:34.120 align:middle line:84%
but we ended up in
a shamanic ceremony

00:09:34.120 --> 00:09:38.290 align:middle line:84%
with a great shaman, a really
great shaman, a Mayan shaman.

00:09:38.290 --> 00:09:41.470 align:middle line:84%
And in that shamanic ceremony--
it was my first ever,

00:09:41.470 --> 00:09:43.940 align:middle line:90%
this was in 1994.

00:09:43.940 --> 00:09:46.980 align:middle line:84%
Even though I'd worked with many
people in different cultures,

00:09:46.980 --> 00:09:49.360 align:middle line:84%
I'd never been in a
shamanic ceremony before

00:09:49.360 --> 00:09:52.290 align:middle line:84%
and I'd never worked in Central
and Latin America or South

00:09:52.290 --> 00:09:53.600 align:middle line:90%
America.

00:09:53.600 --> 00:09:55.970 align:middle line:84%
And the shamanic ceremony
was in the middle

00:09:55.970 --> 00:09:58.500 align:middle line:84%
of the night with a big
fire and we were lying down

00:09:58.500 --> 00:10:00.610 align:middle line:84%
in the fire with our
feet towards the fire.

00:10:00.610 --> 00:10:04.120 align:middle line:84%
The shaman, with John's help,
was drumming and chanting.

00:10:04.120 --> 00:10:06.310 align:middle line:84%
And with John's
help in translation,

00:10:06.310 --> 00:10:07.411 align:middle line:90%
asked us to journey.

00:10:07.411 --> 00:10:08.910 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't even
know what that was

00:10:08.910 --> 00:10:11.450 align:middle line:84%
but I knew it had something
to do with closing your eyes.

00:10:11.450 --> 00:10:14.765 align:middle line:84%
So I did and the night
air and the crackling

00:10:14.765 --> 00:10:18.430 align:middle line:84%
of the fire and the
shaman's chanting,

00:10:18.430 --> 00:10:24.240 align:middle line:84%
his mesmerizing voice, and this
drum beat just transported me.

00:10:24.240 --> 00:10:30.910 align:middle line:84%
And I started to feel my arms
turn into gigantic wings.

00:10:30.910 --> 00:10:35.490 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't my imagination;
it was happening.

00:10:35.490 --> 00:10:38.890 align:middle line:84%
I didn't open my eyes because
I became completely hypnotized

00:10:38.890 --> 00:10:42.020 align:middle line:84%
by this incredible
space we were in.

00:10:42.020 --> 00:10:45.050 align:middle line:84%
And my arms turned into
these gigantic wings,

00:10:45.050 --> 00:10:48.740 align:middle line:84%
and I felt a large curved
beak grow on my face.

00:10:48.740 --> 00:10:53.760 align:middle line:84%
And with sort of a
miraculous next moment,

00:10:53.760 --> 00:10:57.100 align:middle line:84%
I was flying over a
vast unending forest

00:10:57.100 --> 00:10:59.090 align:middle line:90%
of green in slow motion.

00:10:59.090 --> 00:11:02.260 align:middle line:84%
And I was a giant
bird and I could

00:11:02.260 --> 00:11:05.600 align:middle line:84%
see all the way through
the top of the trees,

00:11:05.600 --> 00:11:07.280 align:middle line:84%
through the canopy
to the forest floor

00:11:07.280 --> 00:11:09.779 align:middle line:84%
and see little creatures running
around on the forest floor.

00:11:09.779 --> 00:11:14.320 align:middle line:84%
And as I was flying over this
vast unending forest of green

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:17.210 align:middle line:84%
that went forever,
these disembodied faces

00:11:17.210 --> 00:11:21.320 align:middle line:84%
of men with orange
geometric face paint

00:11:21.320 --> 00:11:24.460 align:middle line:84%
and yellow, red and black
feather crowns on their heads

00:11:24.460 --> 00:11:26.180 align:middle line:84%
started floating
up from the forest

00:11:26.180 --> 00:11:29.100 align:middle line:90%
floor towards me, the bird.

00:11:29.100 --> 00:11:31.320 align:middle line:84%
And they were speaking in
a strange tongue and kind

00:11:31.320 --> 00:11:35.550 align:middle line:84%
of calling to this bird, calling
in a kind of plaintiff call

00:11:35.550 --> 00:11:36.710 align:middle line:90%
to the bird.

00:11:36.710 --> 00:11:39.290 align:middle line:84%
And this is coming at
me-- now, I'm the bird.

00:11:39.290 --> 00:11:41.890 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't
understand the voices

00:11:41.890 --> 00:11:43.090 align:middle line:90%
or what they were saying.

00:11:43.090 --> 00:11:46.130 align:middle line:84%
As they floated back
down into the forest,

00:11:46.130 --> 00:11:49.130 align:middle line:84%
these faces with these
geometric face paint.

00:11:49.130 --> 00:11:52.210 align:middle line:84%
And this went on for I
have no idea how long.

00:11:52.210 --> 00:11:56.130 align:middle line:84%
Kind of like time stopped, it
was endless, I was this bird.

00:11:56.130 --> 00:12:00.680 align:middle line:84%
And then I heard a loud, like
a drumbeat, a loud drumbeat.

00:12:00.680 --> 00:12:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And I realized, oh,
I'm in Guatemala,

00:12:03.190 --> 00:12:05.710 align:middle line:84%
I'm in charge of this
group, I'm a human being.

00:12:05.710 --> 00:12:06.760 align:middle line:90%
What am I doing?

00:12:06.760 --> 00:12:07.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Present time.

00:12:07.760 --> 00:12:10.110 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: And I sat
up and felt my arms.

00:12:10.110 --> 00:12:11.510 align:middle line:90%
They were just as they had been.

00:12:11.510 --> 00:12:12.270 align:middle line:90%
And my face.

00:12:12.270 --> 00:12:14.110 align:middle line:84%
And I looked around
the circle-- and this

00:12:14.110 --> 00:12:16.240 align:middle line:84%
is in the middle the night,
now, dark as can be--

00:12:16.240 --> 00:12:18.040 align:middle line:84%
and the fire had burned
all the way down.

00:12:18.040 --> 00:12:21.560 align:middle line:84%
So I could see the
shaman across the embers.

00:12:21.560 --> 00:12:24.029 align:middle line:84%
And all the people
in the circle were

00:12:24.029 --> 00:12:26.070 align:middle line:84%
kind of like coming out
of some sort of a trance.

00:12:26.070 --> 00:12:28.312 align:middle line:84%
It was really,
really awesome, Lisa.

00:12:28.312 --> 00:12:29.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Powerful.

00:12:29.020 --> 00:12:30.270 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: It was incredible.

00:12:30.270 --> 00:12:33.167 align:middle line:84%
And so each person
shared as best they could

00:12:33.167 --> 00:12:34.250 align:middle line:90%
what had happened to them.

00:12:34.250 --> 00:12:37.030 align:middle line:84%
And everyone had become some
sort of an animal except

00:12:37.030 --> 00:12:39.372 align:middle line:84%
for one person who'd fallen
asleep and dreamt of her

00:12:39.372 --> 00:12:40.830 align:middle line:84%
grandchildren,
which is, I thought,

00:12:40.830 --> 00:12:42.500 align:middle line:84%
what I was going
to do but I didn't.

00:12:42.500 --> 00:12:45.050 align:middle line:84%
And then when it was
my turn, I shared

00:12:45.050 --> 00:12:47.730 align:middle line:84%
with the shaman, which
was his request, what

00:12:47.730 --> 00:12:50.110 align:middle line:90%
I've just shared with you.

00:12:50.110 --> 00:12:53.635 align:middle line:84%
And he looked across at me with
a kind of strange, weird look.

00:12:53.635 --> 00:12:56.060 align:middle line:84%
He was kind of strange,
weird looking person anyway.

00:12:56.060 --> 00:12:58.742 align:middle line:84%
Kind of strange and the
fire underneath his face.

00:12:58.742 --> 00:13:00.700 align:middle line:84%
And then it went all the
way around the circle.

00:13:00.700 --> 00:13:02.660 align:middle line:84%
And then it went to
my friend John Perkins

00:13:02.660 --> 00:13:06.100 align:middle line:84%
who had spent many, many
years working in the Amazon.

00:13:06.100 --> 00:13:11.710 align:middle line:84%
And John had had an-- also had
a vision very similar to mine.

00:13:11.710 --> 00:13:15.560 align:middle line:84%
And when the shaman heard
John speak and went back

00:13:15.560 --> 00:13:18.980 align:middle line:84%
to what I said, he then
completed the ritual

00:13:18.980 --> 00:13:23.630 align:middle line:84%
and asked the two of us to stay
and everybody else departed.

00:13:23.630 --> 00:13:27.200 align:middle line:84%
And John, who had
told me, really,

00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:31.630 align:middle line:84%
for several years about the
Achuar people in the Ecuadorian

00:13:31.630 --> 00:13:33.710 align:middle line:84%
Amazon who he knew
at some point were

00:13:33.710 --> 00:13:39.310 align:middle line:84%
going to be calling for contact,
knew that this was the call.

00:13:39.310 --> 00:13:41.620 align:middle line:84%
That this was the
time, that we were

00:13:41.620 --> 00:13:44.940 align:middle line:84%
being called to meet with
the Achuar people who

00:13:44.940 --> 00:13:47.490 align:middle line:84%
had almost no contact
with the outside world

00:13:47.490 --> 00:13:49.260 align:middle line:90%
and were ready for contact.

00:13:49.260 --> 00:13:51.360 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it came through
you in that moment.

00:13:51.360 --> 00:13:53.380 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: And John I would say.

00:13:53.380 --> 00:13:57.939 align:middle line:84%
And all kinds of different
signs that I could talk about.

00:13:57.939 --> 00:13:58.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Synchronicities--

00:13:58.980 --> 00:13:59.480 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yes.

00:13:59.480 --> 00:14:00.896 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --that
lined up around it.

00:14:00.896 --> 00:14:03.370 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Made it clear
that we needed to go.

00:14:03.370 --> 00:14:04.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That is
a beautiful story

00:14:04.900 --> 00:14:06.820 align:middle line:84%
of what a real true
calling is like.

00:14:06.820 --> 00:14:10.600 align:middle line:84%
So then everything after
that lined up perfectly

00:14:10.600 --> 00:14:13.321 align:middle line:84%
and according to the
vision without your trying.

00:14:13.321 --> 00:14:13.820 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:14:13.820 --> 00:14:16.740 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well, I must
say, I couldn't figure out

00:14:16.740 --> 00:14:18.680 align:middle line:90%
how to do that.

00:14:18.680 --> 00:14:21.390 align:middle line:84%
I was running this
giant Hunger Project

00:14:21.390 --> 00:14:22.764 align:middle line:90%
movement in 47 countries--

00:14:22.764 --> 00:14:23.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Already.

00:14:23.430 --> 00:14:26.900 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: --and I went directly
from Guatemala to Ghana

00:14:26.900 --> 00:14:31.080 align:middle line:84%
to a board meeting with our
Ghanaian board in Ghana.

00:14:31.080 --> 00:14:34.570 align:middle line:84%
And we're sitting around
a table in a hotel,

00:14:34.570 --> 00:14:40.270 align:middle line:84%
in a hotel meeting room--
three women and five men

00:14:40.270 --> 00:14:42.030 align:middle line:84%
and then myself--
all Ghanaian people

00:14:42.030 --> 00:14:44.550 align:middle line:84%
with blue black skin,
beautiful people.

00:14:44.550 --> 00:14:46.790 align:middle line:84%
And we're having this
wonderful conversation

00:14:46.790 --> 00:14:49.260 align:middle line:84%
about the work of the
Hunger Project in Ghana--

00:14:49.260 --> 00:14:52.930 align:middle line:84%
we're in Accra, the capital
city-- and the men are talking

00:14:52.930 --> 00:14:56.100 align:middle line:84%
and in a flash,
suddenly they started

00:14:56.100 --> 00:14:59.550 align:middle line:84%
to have orange geometric face
paint appear on their faces,

00:14:59.550 --> 00:15:00.660 align:middle line:90%
on their blue black faces.

00:15:00.660 --> 00:15:01.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: From what you saw?

00:15:01.020 --> 00:15:01.820 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: In Africa.

00:15:01.820 --> 00:15:02.620 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:15:02.620 --> 00:15:05.560 align:middle line:84%
So I thought, oh, my God, I've
just gone completely nuts.

00:15:05.560 --> 00:15:07.560 align:middle line:84%
And nobody was
talking about this.

00:15:07.560 --> 00:15:10.454 align:middle line:84%
It would be as if you
had something growing out

00:15:10.454 --> 00:15:12.370 align:middle line:84%
of your cheek and we
just kept talking as if--

00:15:12.370 --> 00:15:13.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: All of a sudden.

00:15:13.370 --> 00:15:14.770 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: --it wasn't happening.

00:15:14.770 --> 00:15:18.630 align:middle line:84%
And so I got shaken and
I excused myself and went

00:15:18.630 --> 00:15:21.170 align:middle line:84%
to the ladies' room, came back,
everybody was still talking,

00:15:21.170 --> 00:15:23.260 align:middle line:84%
everything was fine, and
then it happened again.

00:15:23.260 --> 00:15:26.630 align:middle line:84%
And then I really burst into
tears, I started shaking.

00:15:26.630 --> 00:15:27.960 align:middle line:90%
Everyone asks me what's wrong.

00:15:27.960 --> 00:15:31.420 align:middle line:84%
I said, I think
I'm very sick and I

00:15:31.420 --> 00:15:33.060 align:middle line:84%
need to go back to
the United States.

00:15:33.060 --> 00:15:34.180 align:middle line:90%
And I thought I was sick.

00:15:34.180 --> 00:15:36.560 align:middle line:90%
I thought I was hallucinating.

00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:38.050 align:middle line:90%
And perhaps I was, who knows.

00:15:38.050 --> 00:15:41.420 align:middle line:84%
But I ended up going to the
airport, getting on a plane,

00:15:41.420 --> 00:15:43.930 align:middle line:84%
and all the way back
to San Francisco

00:15:43.930 --> 00:15:45.780 align:middle line:90%
I saw these same faces.

00:15:45.780 --> 00:15:47.850 align:middle line:84%
Whether my eyes
were open or shut.

00:15:47.850 --> 00:15:50.240 align:middle line:84%
So by the time I
really returned home

00:15:50.240 --> 00:15:54.030 align:middle line:84%
and-- with John Perkins and I--
we realized, we've got to go.

00:15:54.030 --> 00:15:57.040 align:middle line:84%
We put together a group
of 12 people, which

00:15:57.040 --> 00:15:59.060 align:middle line:90%
is what the Achuar asked for.

00:15:59.060 --> 00:16:01.466 align:middle line:84%
People with open hearts,
people with global voice,

00:16:01.466 --> 00:16:02.840 align:middle line:84%
people who know
the rainforest is

00:16:02.840 --> 00:16:05.040 align:middle line:84%
critical to the
future of life, people

00:16:05.040 --> 00:16:07.490 align:middle line:84%
who know that great
wisdom is coming

00:16:07.490 --> 00:16:09.810 align:middle line:84%
from the shamans of
today, and people

00:16:09.810 --> 00:16:12.700 align:middle line:84%
who knew that indigenous wisdom
is critical for our survival.

00:16:12.700 --> 00:16:15.950 align:middle line:84%
And we traveled down
to South America,

00:16:15.950 --> 00:16:18.160 align:middle line:84%
to Quito, the
capital of Ecuador,

00:16:18.160 --> 00:16:20.440 align:middle line:84%
down the Valley
of the Volcanoes,

00:16:20.440 --> 00:16:22.040 align:middle line:84%
over the eastern
side of the Andes,

00:16:22.040 --> 00:16:24.160 align:middle line:84%
down the Pastaza River canyon--
if you can picture all this.

00:16:24.160 --> 00:16:25.993 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We actually
have some video of that.

00:16:25.993 --> 00:16:29.220 align:middle line:84%
But what a beautiful
story of a true calling.

00:16:29.220 --> 00:16:32.230 align:middle line:84%
But then how you take
action on a calling

00:16:32.230 --> 00:16:36.430 align:middle line:84%
and not just deny it and go back
into the cave or the darkness

00:16:36.430 --> 00:16:39.090 align:middle line:84%
or routine or whatever
you could do to numb it.

00:16:39.090 --> 00:16:40.960 align:middle line:84%
But what it really
means to follow.

00:16:40.960 --> 00:16:44.790 align:middle line:84%
And I want to share
with the viewers of what

00:16:44.790 --> 00:16:46.920 align:middle line:90%
transpired as a result of that.

00:16:46.920 --> 00:16:50.700 align:middle line:84%
We have a clip from the
"Awakening the Dreamer" video,

00:16:50.700 --> 00:16:53.481 align:middle line:84%
and it shows a little bit
about what this mission is

00:16:53.481 --> 00:16:55.230 align:middle line:84%
so that people can
really understand that.

00:16:55.230 --> 00:16:56.120 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look at that.

00:16:56.120 --> 00:16:56.745 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Great.

00:16:56.745 --> 00:16:57.864 align:middle line:90%
Perfect.

00:16:57.864 --> 00:16:58.780 align:middle line:90%
