00:16:58.780 --> 00:17:02.370 align:middle line:84%
>>In 1995, a call issued
forth from the heart

00:17:02.370 --> 00:17:05.030 align:middle line:84%
of the natural world that
was heard thousands of miles

00:17:05.030 --> 00:17:09.119 align:middle line:84%
away by a small group of
people in the modern world.

00:17:09.119 --> 00:17:11.480 align:middle line:84%
In the summer of that
year, in a remote village

00:17:11.480 --> 00:17:15.190 align:middle line:84%
in the rainforest, these
two worlds came together.

00:17:15.190 --> 00:17:17.220 align:middle line:84%
And the Pachamama
Alliance was born.

00:17:17.220 --> 00:17:22.000 align:middle line:90%


00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:24.490 align:middle line:10%
>>From the very beginning,
our indigenous partners

00:17:24.490 --> 00:17:26.242 align:middle line:10%
told us that it was
really, really great

00:17:26.242 --> 00:17:28.450 align:middle line:10%
that we were working with
them in the Amazon shoulder

00:17:28.450 --> 00:17:29.690 align:middle line:10%
to shoulder.

00:17:29.690 --> 00:17:31.830 align:middle line:10%
But that was only
half the battle.

00:17:31.830 --> 00:17:33.570 align:middle line:10%
They told us that
if we really wanted

00:17:33.570 --> 00:17:36.030 align:middle line:10%
to protect their
lands permanently,

00:17:36.030 --> 00:17:39.440 align:middle line:10%
we would need to go to work
in our part of the world.

00:17:39.440 --> 00:17:41.760 align:middle line:84%
And as they put
it, we would need

00:17:41.760 --> 00:17:44.580 align:middle line:84%
to change the
dream of the north,

00:17:44.580 --> 00:17:47.380 align:middle line:90%
the dream of the modern world.

00:17:47.380 --> 00:17:50.660 align:middle line:84%
A dream rooted in
consumption and acquisition,

00:17:50.660 --> 00:17:52.810 align:middle line:84%
without any regard
to the consequences

00:17:52.810 --> 00:17:56.420 align:middle line:84%
to the natural world
or even our own future.

00:17:56.420 --> 00:17:58.480 align:middle line:10%
>>Changing the dream
of the modern world

00:17:58.480 --> 00:18:00.850 align:middle line:10%
is certainly a daunting
and some would even

00:18:00.850 --> 00:18:02.660 align:middle line:10%
say an impossible task.

00:18:02.660 --> 00:18:06.850 align:middle line:10%
But we took the request of
the Achuar very seriously.

00:18:06.850 --> 00:18:09.070 align:middle line:10%
Out of our work
with them, we came

00:18:09.070 --> 00:18:11.230 align:middle line:10%
to see that we in
the modern world

00:18:11.230 --> 00:18:14.560 align:middle line:10%
truly are in some kind
of a trance, living

00:18:14.560 --> 00:18:17.140 align:middle line:10%
in a dream that's
threatening to destroy

00:18:17.140 --> 00:18:20.470 align:middle line:10%
not only the rainforest
and their way of life,

00:18:20.470 --> 00:18:23.860 align:middle line:10%
but the health and well
being of our entire planet.

00:18:23.860 --> 00:18:27.860 align:middle line:84%
Our society is on a
completely unsustainable path,

00:18:27.860 --> 00:18:30.150 align:middle line:84%
and experts
everywhere are saying

00:18:30.150 --> 00:18:32.600 align:middle line:84%
that we have a limited
time to turn things around.

00:18:32.600 --> 00:18:40.830 align:middle line:90%


00:18:40.830 --> 00:18:42.440 align:middle line:10%
>>So in response
to the request that

00:18:42.440 --> 00:18:44.310 align:middle line:10%
came from its
indigenous partners,

00:18:44.310 --> 00:18:47.370 align:middle line:10%
the Pachamama Alliance
created this symposium,

00:18:47.370 --> 00:18:50.080 align:middle line:10%
Awakening the Dreamer,
Changing the Dream.

00:18:50.080 --> 00:18:52.290 align:middle line:10%
Now being offered by
thousands of volunteers

00:18:52.290 --> 00:18:54.190 align:middle line:10%
in dozens of countries
around the world.

00:18:54.190 --> 00:18:58.270 align:middle line:90%


00:18:58.270 --> 00:19:01.070 align:middle line:84%
The purpose of the symposium
is an audacious one,

00:19:01.070 --> 00:19:03.660 align:middle line:84%
bringing forth an
environmentally sustainable,

00:19:03.660 --> 00:19:07.070 align:middle line:84%
spiritually fulfilling,
socially just human presence

00:19:07.070 --> 00:19:07.700 align:middle line:90%
on this planet.

00:19:07.700 --> 00:19:12.155 align:middle line:90%


00:19:12.155 --> 00:19:14.620 align:middle line:10%
>>The intention is
that, by the end,

00:19:14.620 --> 00:19:17.850 align:middle line:10%
rather than seeing these
as three separate issues,

00:19:17.850 --> 00:19:21.370 align:middle line:10%
you see them as
interrelated facets of one

00:19:21.370 --> 00:19:25.090 align:middle line:10%
profoundly interconnected whole.

00:19:25.090 --> 00:19:28.240 align:middle line:84%
And that you not only
understand the scope and urgency

00:19:28.240 --> 00:19:30.960 align:middle line:84%
of the planetary
situation we face,

00:19:30.960 --> 00:19:34.260 align:middle line:84%
but you also see that the
possibility of our times

00:19:34.260 --> 00:19:35.835 align:middle line:90%
is greater than the crisis.

00:19:35.835 --> 00:19:41.247 align:middle line:90%


00:19:41.247 --> 00:19:42.080 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:19:42.080 --> 00:19:47.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that entire video
inspired a movement, basically,

00:19:47.420 --> 00:19:50.490 align:middle line:84%
that created then a
symposium, a class, that

00:19:50.490 --> 00:19:51.569 align:middle line:90%
was done here at Gaiam.

00:19:51.569 --> 00:19:52.110 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yes.

00:19:52.110 --> 00:19:52.880 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:19:52.880 --> 00:19:56.010 align:middle line:84%
Well, as it says in
the video, we really

00:19:56.010 --> 00:19:57.940 align:middle line:84%
got the message from
the indigenous people

00:19:57.940 --> 00:20:01.050 align:middle line:84%
that the real work--
obviously they

00:20:01.050 --> 00:20:04.140 align:middle line:84%
wanted us to stand with them
to protect their forests.

00:20:04.140 --> 00:20:09.300 align:middle line:84%
And one of our
great statements is

00:20:09.300 --> 00:20:11.130 align:middle line:84%
we're committed to
preserving the world's

00:20:11.130 --> 00:20:12.920 align:middle line:84%
tropical rainforest,
but by empowering

00:20:12.920 --> 00:20:16.090 align:middle line:84%
the indigenous people who
are its natural custodians.

00:20:16.090 --> 00:20:18.330 align:middle line:84%
But also, it's very
clear that what's

00:20:18.330 --> 00:20:19.940 align:middle line:84%
putting pressure
on the ecosystems--

00:20:19.940 --> 00:20:22.490 align:middle line:84%
particularly the rainforests
but on all ecosystems--

00:20:22.490 --> 00:20:24.922 align:middle line:84%
is the dream or trance
of the modern world which

00:20:24.922 --> 00:20:26.380 align:middle line:84%
is, it said in the
video, is really

00:20:26.380 --> 00:20:28.610 align:middle line:84%
where Pachamama
has gone to work.

00:20:28.610 --> 00:20:32.180 align:middle line:84%
And this program, the Awakening
the Dream or Changing the Dream

00:20:32.180 --> 00:20:34.500 align:middle line:90%
symposium now has many forms.

00:20:34.500 --> 00:20:39.645 align:middle line:84%
One of them is this wonderful
live TV-- television Gaiam

00:20:39.645 --> 00:20:40.145 align:middle line:90%
version.

00:20:40.145 --> 00:20:40.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:20:40.470 --> 00:20:40.940 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Video.

00:20:40.940 --> 00:20:41.856 align:middle line:90%
I guess it's not live.

00:20:41.856 --> 00:20:43.310 align:middle line:90%
It was live and now it's video.

00:20:43.310 --> 00:20:45.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But now people have
brought it into their own homes

00:20:45.060 --> 00:20:45.390 align:middle line:90%
and--

00:20:45.390 --> 00:20:45.710 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Oh, yes.

00:20:45.710 --> 00:20:46.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --created it
all around the world.

00:20:46.880 --> 00:20:49.088 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: There's thousands
of facilitators delivering

00:20:49.088 --> 00:20:53.260 align:middle line:84%
the symposium in 62 countries
