>>LISA: --adopted and
all that can be found

00:21:07.300 --> 00:21:08.161 align:middle line:90%
on an Gaiamtv.com--

00:21:08.161 --> 00:21:08.660 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yes

00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:09.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --as well.

00:21:09.410 --> 00:21:10.500 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Absolutely.

00:21:10.500 --> 00:21:13.124 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So then this-- what does
Pachamama, by the way, mean?

00:21:13.124 --> 00:21:14.540 align:middle line:84%
What is the name,
Pachamama, mean?

00:21:14.540 --> 00:21:16.370 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well, the word
pachamama, first of all,

00:21:16.370 --> 00:21:17.630 align:middle line:90%
is from the Quechua people.

00:21:17.630 --> 00:21:20.890 align:middle line:84%
The Quechua people, the largest
indigenous language group

00:21:20.890 --> 00:21:22.020 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:21:22.020 --> 00:21:25.090 align:middle line:84%
And they live in the
Andes and in the Amazon.

00:21:25.090 --> 00:21:27.440 align:middle line:84%
And the word pachamama
means mother earth.

00:21:27.440 --> 00:21:28.850 align:middle line:90%
Pacha mama.

00:21:28.850 --> 00:21:32.260 align:middle line:84%
But to Quechua people, they
would say the earth, the sky,

00:21:32.260 --> 00:21:34.170 align:middle line:90%
the universe, and all time.

00:21:34.170 --> 00:21:37.150 align:middle line:84%
Because indigenous people
live in a very large cosmology

00:21:37.150 --> 00:21:40.607 align:middle line:84%
about reality, much more-- they
see much more than this chair.

00:21:40.607 --> 00:21:42.440 align:middle line:84%
They see the spirit of
the chair, et cetera.

00:21:42.440 --> 00:21:46.930 align:middle line:84%
So it means the earth, the
sky, the universe and all time.

00:21:46.930 --> 00:21:48.880 align:middle line:84%
And so the Pachamama
Alliance is an alliance

00:21:48.880 --> 00:21:51.800 align:middle line:84%
between indigenous peoples
of the Amazon and the Andes

00:21:51.800 --> 00:21:54.510 align:middle line:84%
and conscious committed people
in the modern world like you

00:21:54.510 --> 00:21:55.010 align:middle line:90%
and me.

00:21:55.010 --> 00:21:56.940 align:middle line:84%
And I think probably
everybody who's watching this.

00:21:56.940 --> 00:21:58.314 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And
inspiring, of course,

00:21:58.314 --> 00:22:00.610 align:middle line:84%
people on how they can
change and make a difference.

00:22:00.610 --> 00:22:03.392 align:middle line:84%
So you talked about that
trance of the modern world.

00:22:03.392 --> 00:22:05.350 align:middle line:84%
We've been touching on
that throughout the show

00:22:05.350 --> 00:22:08.270 align:middle line:84%
because it-- the further
and further we get away

00:22:08.270 --> 00:22:10.784 align:middle line:84%
from the Amazon and
these indigenous people,

00:22:10.784 --> 00:22:12.700 align:middle line:84%
and the more that we get
into our modern world

00:22:12.700 --> 00:22:16.160 align:middle line:84%
with the modern conveniences and
convenience stores and packaged

00:22:16.160 --> 00:22:19.070 align:middle line:84%
foods and all that goes
along with our modern world,

00:22:19.070 --> 00:22:21.510 align:middle line:84%
it takes people like
you to bring us back

00:22:21.510 --> 00:22:24.670 align:middle line:84%
into that consciousness
and movements

00:22:24.670 --> 00:22:26.840 align:middle line:84%
like this to bring us back
into that consciousness.

00:22:26.840 --> 00:22:30.070 align:middle line:84%
So, actually there's another
clip that I want people to see,

00:22:30.070 --> 00:22:32.410 align:middle line:84%
and this has to do
with what that means.

00:22:32.410 --> 00:22:36.190 align:middle line:84%
What it actually means
to reconnect to--

00:22:36.190 --> 00:22:37.060 align:middle line:90%
what do you call it?

00:22:37.060 --> 00:22:39.329 align:middle line:84%
You called it
unexamined assumptions.

00:22:39.329 --> 00:22:39.870 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yes.

00:22:39.870 --> 00:22:41.453 align:middle line:84%
One of the things
that is so beautiful

00:22:41.453 --> 00:22:44.209 align:middle line:84%
about indigenous peoples,
and our indigenous partners

00:22:44.209 --> 00:22:46.000 align:middle line:84%
in particular, is they
don't make us wrong.

00:22:46.000 --> 00:22:46.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, I like it.

00:22:46.970 --> 00:22:48.030 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: I love that.

00:22:48.030 --> 00:22:48.571 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:22:48.571 --> 00:22:49.080 align:middle line:90%
Me, too.

00:22:49.080 --> 00:22:51.780 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: What they see is
that we're in a trance.

00:22:51.780 --> 00:22:54.660 align:middle line:84%
They're not in it, so they
can see that we're in it.

00:22:54.660 --> 00:22:57.660 align:middle line:84%
And what they are--
see that their role is

00:22:57.660 --> 00:22:59.990 align:middle line:84%
is to help us to wake
up from the trance

00:22:59.990 --> 00:23:01.860 align:middle line:90%
before it takes us off a cliff.

00:23:01.860 --> 00:23:04.610 align:middle line:84%
And so the trance
is actually made up

00:23:04.610 --> 00:23:07.840 align:middle line:84%
of unconscious,
unexamined assumptions.

00:23:07.840 --> 00:23:10.440 align:middle line:84%
Kind of a misunderstanding
of our place in the world.

00:23:10.440 --> 00:23:13.110 align:middle line:84%
And it's not-- we're
not flawed as a species,

00:23:13.110 --> 00:23:16.600 align:middle line:90%
we're really merely mistaken.

00:23:16.600 --> 00:23:18.890 align:middle line:84%
We've isolated
ourselves as a species

00:23:18.890 --> 00:23:22.460 align:middle line:84%
and we have unconscious
assumptions like, for example,

00:23:22.460 --> 00:23:27.260 align:middle line:84%
when you throw something
away, where is away?

00:23:27.260 --> 00:23:28.337 align:middle line:90%
There's no such place.

00:23:28.337 --> 00:23:28.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:23:28.920 --> 00:23:29.919 align:middle line:90%
Where does it really go?

00:23:29.919 --> 00:23:31.930 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: We've created
an unconscious assumption

00:23:31.930 --> 00:23:32.980 align:middle line:90%
that there is an away.

00:23:32.980 --> 00:23:33.750 align:middle line:90%
But there isn't.

00:23:33.750 --> 00:23:36.690 align:middle line:84%
Even in space now is
cluttered with debris.

00:23:36.690 --> 00:23:40.360 align:middle line:84%
So to actually let go of
an unconscious unexamined

00:23:40.360 --> 00:23:42.620 align:middle line:84%
assumption like
there is an away,

00:23:42.620 --> 00:23:46.937 align:middle line:84%
is a very profound way of
shifting your relationship

00:23:46.937 --> 00:23:48.020 align:middle line:90%
with the world around you.

00:23:48.020 --> 00:23:48.895 align:middle line:90%
So that's an example.

00:23:48.895 --> 00:23:50.019 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There's a lot more.

00:23:50.019 --> 00:23:52.370 align:middle line:84%
I want actually to see--
want you see this clip again

00:23:52.370 --> 00:23:53.850 align:middle line:90%
from "Awakening the Dreamer."

00:23:53.850 --> 00:23:58.168 align:middle line:84%
It talks all about
unconscious assumptions.

00:23:58.168 --> 00:23:59.570 align:middle line:90%
[BEGIN VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:23:59.570 --> 00:24:02.240 align:middle line:84%
>>According to Thomas
Berry, our industrial age

00:24:02.240 --> 00:24:03.970 align:middle line:84%
could be characterized
as a period

00:24:03.970 --> 00:24:07.250 align:middle line:84%
of technological entrancement
in which our obsession

00:24:07.250 --> 00:24:11.270 align:middle line:84%
progress has us marching toward
an ill-defined magical paradise

00:24:11.270 --> 00:24:13.670 align:middle line:90%
somewhere in the future.

00:24:13.670 --> 00:24:15.960 align:middle line:84%
A future in which we
have mastered the Earth

00:24:15.960 --> 00:24:18.430 align:middle line:84%
and everything on it
without any limits.

00:24:18.430 --> 00:24:21.620 align:middle line:90%


00:24:21.620 --> 00:24:25.390 align:middle line:84%
And so it could be said
that we in the modern world

00:24:25.390 --> 00:24:28.360 align:middle line:90%
are living in a kind of trance.

00:24:28.360 --> 00:24:30.135 align:middle line:84%
Indigenous people
would call this trance

00:24:30.135 --> 00:24:33.150 align:middle line:90%
the dream of the modern world.

00:24:33.150 --> 00:24:36.940 align:middle line:10%
This dream could also be
called our current worldview,

00:24:36.940 --> 00:24:41.880 align:middle line:10%
a way of seeing the world we're
not even aware that we have.

00:24:41.880 --> 00:24:43.940 align:middle line:10%
A worldview is held
in place by a set

00:24:43.940 --> 00:24:46.130 align:middle line:10%
of beliefs and
unexamined assumptions

00:24:46.130 --> 00:24:48.520 align:middle line:10%
that we're completely
unaware of.

00:24:48.520 --> 00:24:50.835 align:middle line:10%
Like glasses we've worn
so long we don't even

00:24:50.835 --> 00:24:54.470 align:middle line:10%
know we're looking
through them anymore.

00:24:54.470 --> 00:24:57.870 align:middle line:10%
People's actions correlate
with their worldview.

00:24:57.870 --> 00:25:01.320 align:middle line:10%
We take actions consistent
with how we see the world.

00:25:01.320 --> 00:25:03.930 align:middle line:84%
And often those actions
produce outcomes

00:25:03.930 --> 00:25:07.520 align:middle line:90%
we didn't predict or intend.

00:25:07.520 --> 00:25:12.230 align:middle line:84%
So when our actions produce
outcomes we're not intending,

00:25:12.230 --> 00:25:15.070 align:middle line:84%
it's important to identify
the unconscious unexamined

00:25:15.070 --> 00:25:18.280 align:middle line:84%
assumptions that generated those
actions in the first place.

00:25:18.280 --> 00:25:20.870 align:middle line:90%


00:25:20.870 --> 00:25:23.170 align:middle line:84%
>>All the crises
we're facing today

00:25:23.170 --> 00:25:25.610 align:middle line:84%
can be seen as the
unintended result

00:25:25.610 --> 00:25:27.850 align:middle line:84%
of the unexamined
assumptions that

00:25:27.850 --> 00:25:33.084 align:middle line:84%
permeate the modern industrial
society and our own thinking.

00:25:33.084 --> 00:25:34.060 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:25:34.060 --> 00:25:36.230 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So as we can see,
it's all about awareness,

00:25:36.230 --> 00:25:38.300 align:middle line:84%
it's all about
decisions that we make,

00:25:38.300 --> 00:25:40.200 align:middle line:84%
it's all about
starting somewhere.

00:25:40.200 --> 00:25:43.180 align:middle line:84%
I love the idea of not making
us wrong because there's

00:25:43.180 --> 00:25:45.660 align:middle line:84%
social means and conveniences
that have gotten us

00:25:45.660 --> 00:25:47.060 align:middle line:90%
into one place or another.

00:25:47.060 --> 00:25:49.750 align:middle line:84%
So what types of things
do you do in your life?

00:25:49.750 --> 00:25:52.570 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well, one of the things
that was a big wake up for me--

00:25:52.570 --> 00:25:54.710 align:middle line:84%
I'll just say it
honest and true,

00:25:54.710 --> 00:26:00.360 align:middle line:84%
to be transparent-- I used to
probably use three, four, five,

00:26:00.360 --> 00:26:03.180 align:middle line:84%
six water bottles a day--
plastic water bottles-- I mean,

00:26:03.180 --> 00:26:06.040 align:middle line:90%
really sort of unconsciously.

00:26:06.040 --> 00:26:07.587 align:middle line:84%
And I was totally
into drinking water

00:26:07.587 --> 00:26:08.920 align:middle line:90%
and it was all about my health--

00:26:08.920 --> 00:26:09.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Good for you.

00:26:09.410 --> 00:26:09.800 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:26:09.800 --> 00:26:11.420 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: --not drinking water
from the tap and all that.

00:26:11.420 --> 00:26:13.170 align:middle line:90%
And this is some time ago now.

00:26:13.170 --> 00:26:14.850 align:middle line:90%
I've totally let go of this.

00:26:14.850 --> 00:26:16.650 align:middle line:84%
But when I took--
when we started

00:26:16.650 --> 00:26:20.250 align:middle line:84%
developing the symposium, and
we actually did the research

00:26:20.250 --> 00:26:22.480 align:middle line:84%
and found out that
in the United States

00:26:22.480 --> 00:26:28.750 align:middle line:84%
alone we discard 600 million
water bottles every single day.

00:26:28.750 --> 00:26:29.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Day.

00:26:29.250 --> 00:26:30.620 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:26:30.620 --> 00:26:32.510 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: That just blew my mind.

00:26:32.510 --> 00:26:34.920 align:middle line:84%
And I learned about this
island out in the middle

00:26:34.920 --> 00:26:37.820 align:middle line:84%
of the ocean of plastic
bottles that's bigger than--

00:26:37.820 --> 00:26:38.903 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The garbage patch.

00:26:38.903 --> 00:26:40.300 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: --Texas.

00:26:40.300 --> 00:26:41.730 align:middle line:90%
I was so shocked by that.

00:26:41.730 --> 00:26:43.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And there's
three of them.

00:26:43.250 --> 00:26:45.950 align:middle line:84%
>>And then I looked
back at my own behavior

00:26:45.950 --> 00:26:49.360 align:middle line:84%
to see, what am I
doing that's actually

00:26:49.360 --> 00:26:52.297 align:middle line:84%
fostering that, fomenting
that, kind of adding to that?

00:26:52.297 --> 00:26:52.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:26:52.880 --> 00:26:55.984 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: And so I almost
never, if I can help it--

00:26:55.984 --> 00:26:57.400 align:middle line:84%
and every once in
a while you have

00:26:57.400 --> 00:27:01.200 align:middle line:84%
to-- take a plastic
bottle of any kind.

00:27:01.200 --> 00:27:02.700 align:middle line:84%
Because I think
about that island,

00:27:02.700 --> 00:27:04.440 align:middle line:84%
I think about that
600 million, and I

00:27:04.440 --> 00:27:06.680 align:middle line:84%
think about the fact
that just me in one

00:27:06.680 --> 00:27:08.770 align:middle line:84%
week, if I did five
water bottles a day

00:27:08.770 --> 00:27:12.910 align:middle line:84%
times seven, that's a lot of
water bottles from just one

00:27:12.910 --> 00:27:13.410 align:middle line:90%
person.

00:27:13.410 --> 00:27:14.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What you were
personally contributing.

00:27:14.190 --> 00:27:16.530 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: And I'm running
conferences with water bottles.

00:27:16.530 --> 00:27:19.860 align:middle line:84%
And so I-- that's so simple
and most people know that now,

00:27:19.860 --> 00:27:21.480 align:middle line:90%
but some people don't.

00:27:21.480 --> 00:27:23.090 align:middle line:84%
And when you find
that out-- and I

00:27:23.090 --> 00:27:25.298 align:middle line:84%
was in a meeting in New
York-- I'll never forget it--

00:27:25.298 --> 00:27:28.030 align:middle line:84%
and there was this really
cool guy from Germany.

00:27:28.030 --> 00:27:30.710 align:middle line:84%
I wish I could remember
his last name because he

00:27:30.710 --> 00:27:32.430 align:middle line:84%
was-- made such
difference to me.

00:27:32.430 --> 00:27:33.670 align:middle line:90%
His name is Siggy.

00:27:33.670 --> 00:27:35.650 align:middle line:84%
And we were-- it was
at the Tibet House

00:27:35.650 --> 00:27:36.820 align:middle line:90%
and we were having lunch.

00:27:36.820 --> 00:27:40.100 align:middle line:84%
And I was doing some
consulting because I

00:27:40.100 --> 00:27:42.520 align:middle line:84%
do fundraising consulting and
organizational development

00:27:42.520 --> 00:27:44.570 align:middle line:90%
consulting sometimes.

00:27:44.570 --> 00:27:46.240 align:middle line:84%
And it was time
for lunch and they

00:27:46.240 --> 00:27:48.640 align:middle line:84%
brought in all this
wonderful food.

00:27:48.640 --> 00:27:52.850 align:middle line:84%
And Siggy would not allow
anyone to take a water bottle.

00:27:52.850 --> 00:27:56.470 align:middle line:84%
He said, I want to just
announce that anybody here

00:27:56.470 --> 00:27:58.942 align:middle line:84%
who doesn't know, we
should not be drinking out

00:27:58.942 --> 00:27:59.650 align:middle line:90%
of water bottles.

00:27:59.650 --> 00:28:04.210 align:middle line:84%
And please take those away and
bring us a pitcher of water

00:28:04.210 --> 00:28:05.380 align:middle line:90%
and put it in a glass.

00:28:05.380 --> 00:28:07.800 align:middle line:84%
And I remember-- it was so
brave of him to do that.

00:28:07.800 --> 00:28:08.990 align:middle line:90%
But then he explained.

00:28:08.990 --> 00:28:12.720 align:middle line:84%
And everybody from then on
from that little gathering

00:28:12.720 --> 00:28:15.490 align:middle line:84%
actually had a more
conscious relationship

00:28:15.490 --> 00:28:16.520 align:middle line:90%
with plastic bottles.

00:28:16.520 --> 00:28:19.280 align:middle line:84%
Now, maybe they don't all never
take another plastic bottle,

00:28:19.280 --> 00:28:21.820 align:middle line:84%
but every one of us can
do something like that

00:28:21.820 --> 00:28:23.230 align:middle line:90%
without making anyone wrong.

00:28:23.230 --> 00:28:24.190 align:middle line:90%
But just awaken.

00:28:24.190 --> 00:28:25.087 align:middle line:90%
Did you know?

00:28:25.087 --> 00:28:25.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:28:25.670 --> 00:28:26.170 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:28:26.170 --> 00:28:29.080 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: And then things
like, for the environment,

00:28:29.080 --> 00:28:32.670 align:middle line:84%
we all know that it's really
better to buy local food

00:28:32.670 --> 00:28:33.630 align:middle line:90%
if you can.

00:28:33.630 --> 00:28:36.525 align:middle line:84%
Now, you can't always do that,
but if you're eating something

00:28:36.525 --> 00:28:41.170 align:middle line:84%
that comes all the way from
France or an Evian bottle,

00:28:41.170 --> 00:28:43.740 align:middle line:84%
you could say, or let's
just say something

00:28:43.740 --> 00:28:49.070 align:middle line:84%
that gets imported from
Australia or New Zealand,

00:28:49.070 --> 00:28:52.680 align:middle line:84%
perhaps a kiwi,
when you could buy

00:28:52.680 --> 00:28:56.237 align:middle line:84%
one that was grown 100
miles away or 50 miles away.

00:28:56.237 --> 00:28:56.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:28:56.820 --> 00:28:59.870 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: You think about how
much petroleum and air travel

00:28:59.870 --> 00:29:04.910 align:middle line:84%
and packaging and-- it takes to
get that little kiwi from New

00:29:04.910 --> 00:29:06.959 align:middle line:84%
Zealand to your table
in San Francisco,

00:29:06.959 --> 00:29:08.500 align:middle line:84%
and you start
thinking, well, I don't

00:29:08.500 --> 00:29:10.300 align:middle line:90%
think I want to do that anymore.

00:29:10.300 --> 00:29:12.330 align:middle line:84%
I'll just look in
my store, where's

00:29:12.330 --> 00:29:13.440 align:middle line:90%
the locally grown food--

00:29:13.440 --> 00:29:14.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Just to be aware of it.

00:29:14.390 --> 00:29:15.930 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: --and if they don't
have it I'll mention that

00:29:15.930 --> 00:29:18.426 align:middle line:84%
to the grocer and then I'll--
I'll say I'm going to go

00:29:18.426 --> 00:29:20.800 align:middle line:84%
to Whole Foods until you have
that section because I know

00:29:20.800 --> 00:29:21.286 align:middle line:90%
they do that.

00:29:21.286 --> 00:29:22.661 align:middle line:84%
Or I'll go to this
grocery store.

00:29:22.661 --> 00:29:23.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I saw this.

00:29:23.770 --> 00:29:25.930 align:middle line:84%
I thought about how far
away we have gotten.

00:29:25.930 --> 00:29:28.119 align:middle line:84%
And I saw this
billboard on the way

00:29:28.119 --> 00:29:29.660 align:middle line:84%
to dropping my
daughter off to school

00:29:29.660 --> 00:29:33.190 align:middle line:84%
and it was a governmental,
I think, health agency.

00:29:33.190 --> 00:29:36.290 align:middle line:84%
And it said something
about-- it was

00:29:36.290 --> 00:29:37.790 align:middle line:84%
this little child
eating watermelon.

00:29:37.790 --> 00:29:40.110 align:middle line:84%
And it said, tell them
it's astronaut food.

00:29:40.110 --> 00:29:41.730 align:middle line:90%
Whatever works.

00:29:41.730 --> 00:29:44.350 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, how
far away have we

00:29:44.350 --> 00:29:48.250 align:middle line:84%
gotten that we need to tell
kids that eating a watermelon

00:29:48.250 --> 00:29:49.800 align:middle line:90%
is astronaut food?

00:29:49.800 --> 00:29:52.450 align:middle line:84%
Why can't we just tell
them it's a watermelon?

00:29:52.450 --> 00:29:54.960 align:middle line:84%
Why did we have to say
that as a campaign?

00:29:54.960 --> 00:29:57.980 align:middle line:84%
That we've gotten so conditioned
by the plastics and the foods

00:29:57.980 --> 00:29:58.660 align:middle line:90%
and so forth.

00:29:58.660 --> 00:30:00.460 align:middle line:84%
But it's all about
the awareness.

00:30:00.460 --> 00:30:02.340 align:middle line:84%
The billboard was
just shocking to me

00:30:02.340 --> 00:30:05.460 align:middle line:84%
that that's now a
marketing campaign.

00:30:05.460 --> 00:30:08.770 align:middle line:84%
But it's about getting back
to-- so when you go back

00:30:08.770 --> 00:30:11.670 align:middle line:84%
to the Amazon, when you go
back to the indigenous people

00:30:11.670 --> 00:30:13.939 align:middle line:84%
there-- and you go
back often, don't you?

00:30:13.939 --> 00:30:14.730 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yes, I do.

00:30:14.730 --> 00:30:15.910 align:middle line:90%
And I take people there, too.

00:30:15.910 --> 00:30:16.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you
take people there.

00:30:16.860 --> 00:30:17.810 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: I'll take
you if you want to go.

00:30:17.810 --> 00:30:18.601 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my God.

00:30:18.601 --> 00:30:20.440 align:middle line:90%
That's an honor to go with you.

00:30:20.440 --> 00:30:24.860 align:middle line:84%
So do you bring this
experience back to the people

00:30:24.860 --> 00:30:27.130 align:middle line:84%
there and say, well,
this is what we've done?

00:30:27.130 --> 00:30:29.560 align:middle line:84%
Is it making an impact,
is really my question?

00:30:29.560 --> 00:30:32.310 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well, yes, is the
answer to that question.

00:30:32.310 --> 00:30:36.020 align:middle line:84%
Then I need to embellish because
when people go on a Pachamama

00:30:36.020 --> 00:30:40.360 align:middle line:84%
Alliance journey, or go to the
Amazon with us, in particular,

00:30:40.360 --> 00:30:44.760 align:middle line:84%
and go to this very remote area,
what you really get from that

00:30:44.760 --> 00:30:46.810 align:middle line:84%
is you get in touch
with something

00:30:46.810 --> 00:30:49.380 align:middle line:84%
that I don't know you can
get in touch with it--

00:30:49.380 --> 00:30:51.900 align:middle line:84%
maybe there are other
ways-- but you actually

00:30:51.900 --> 00:30:54.990 align:middle line:84%
have a relationship
with plants and animals

00:30:54.990 --> 00:30:57.110 align:middle line:90%
like they're your kin.

00:30:57.110 --> 00:30:58.730 align:middle line:84%
Because the indigenous
people, they

00:30:58.730 --> 00:31:00.540 align:middle line:84%
see the giant otter
as their brother

00:31:00.540 --> 00:31:03.730 align:middle line:84%
and the harpy eagle
as their uncle,

00:31:03.730 --> 00:31:08.280 align:middle line:84%
and they see the ayahuasca
plant or the medicinal plants

00:31:08.280 --> 00:31:12.230 align:middle line:84%
or the teaching plants or the
food plants as their relations.

00:31:12.230 --> 00:31:16.010 align:middle line:84%
And they don't live in the
forest off all this stuff.

00:31:16.010 --> 00:31:20.090 align:middle line:84%
They are of the forest and they
live in the community of life

00:31:20.090 --> 00:31:22.380 align:middle line:90%
with all their kin.

00:31:22.380 --> 00:31:24.950 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not saying that you
and I are going to probably

00:31:24.950 --> 00:31:26.260 align:middle line:90%
do that a lot this lifetime.

00:31:26.260 --> 00:31:29.300 align:middle line:84%
But it changes your very
way of seeing the world.

00:31:29.300 --> 00:31:33.410 align:middle line:84%
And plus, they have a
real dignity and respect

00:31:33.410 --> 00:31:36.940 align:middle line:84%
with their ancestors and
with all future generations.

00:31:36.940 --> 00:31:41.910 align:middle line:84%
So you start to realize, oh, I'm
the current blossom on the tree

00:31:41.910 --> 00:31:44.950 align:middle line:84%
of life from the
lineage that I come from

00:31:44.950 --> 00:31:48.370 align:middle line:84%
and I'm passing it onto your
daughter or my children,

00:31:48.370 --> 00:31:51.890 align:middle line:84%
and to do the best job I
can with this period of life

00:31:51.890 --> 00:31:53.550 align:middle line:90%
that I've been given to live.

00:31:53.550 --> 00:31:56.910 align:middle line:84%
You start thinking of yourself
beyond your own lifetime.

00:31:56.910 --> 00:31:58.720 align:middle line:84%
And really, almost
everybody does that.

00:31:58.720 --> 00:32:01.140 align:middle line:90%
And that changes everything.

00:32:01.140 --> 00:32:02.156 align:middle line:90%
I can't tell you.

00:32:02.156 --> 00:32:04.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You're a part of
a much, much bigger whole.

00:32:04.280 --> 00:32:05.140 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: A bigger story.

00:32:05.140 --> 00:32:06.973 align:middle line:84%
And instead of what's
right in front of you,

00:32:06.973 --> 00:32:09.960 align:middle line:84%
all these little petty
worries, they start to diminish

00:32:09.960 --> 00:32:11.330 align:middle line:90%
and they don't have you.

00:32:11.330 --> 00:32:12.790 align:middle line:84%
They don't grip
you like they did.

00:32:12.790 --> 00:32:15.540 align:middle line:84%
So it's really healthy
for your own consciousness

00:32:15.540 --> 00:32:16.700 align:middle line:90%
and your own peace of mind.

00:32:16.700 --> 00:32:19.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Tell me a little bit
more about the ayahuasca plant.

00:32:19.200 --> 00:32:21.550 align:middle line:84%
You had mentioned
that it had-- it's

00:32:21.550 --> 00:32:24.895 align:middle line:84%
meaning to the indigenous people
and what your experience is.

00:32:24.895 --> 00:32:27.020 align:middle line:84%
If you could share with us
a little bit about that.

00:32:27.020 --> 00:32:28.103 align:middle line:90%
I've heard a lot about it.

00:32:28.103 --> 00:32:30.550 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well,
ayahuasca is-- or natem,

00:32:30.550 --> 00:32:33.149 align:middle line:84%
is how the Achuar which
is the primary indigenous

00:32:33.149 --> 00:32:33.940 align:middle line:90%
group we work with.

00:32:33.940 --> 00:32:35.565 align:middle line:84%
We work with all the
indigenous groups,

00:32:35.565 --> 00:32:37.810 align:middle line:84%
but that's the
word that they use.

00:32:37.810 --> 00:32:38.880 align:middle line:90%
Is a teaching plant.

00:32:38.880 --> 00:32:42.580 align:middle line:84%
And its their most sacred,
most revered teacher.

00:32:42.580 --> 00:32:47.440 align:middle line:84%
And it's not a drug, it's
not done in a laboratory,

00:32:47.440 --> 00:32:48.920 align:middle line:90%
it's not a bunch of chemicals.

00:32:48.920 --> 00:32:50.750 align:middle line:90%
It's actually a plant.

00:32:50.750 --> 00:32:54.150 align:middle line:84%
And the shamans prepare
it with great reverence.

00:32:54.150 --> 00:32:54.690 align:middle line:90%
It's-

00:32:54.690 --> 00:32:55.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's ceremonial.

00:32:55.690 --> 00:32:56.231 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yes.

00:32:56.231 --> 00:32:58.690 align:middle line:90%
It's a ceremonial experience.

00:32:58.690 --> 00:33:03.840 align:middle line:84%
And then they are
the people who you

00:33:03.840 --> 00:33:07.080 align:middle line:84%
work with when you
ingest the kind of brew

00:33:07.080 --> 00:33:08.880 align:middle line:90%
that they make out of the plant.

00:33:08.880 --> 00:33:10.370 align:middle line:84%
And I can tell you
this will never

00:33:10.370 --> 00:33:14.240 align:middle line:84%
become a recreational activity
because it makes you very sick.

00:33:14.240 --> 00:33:17.000 align:middle line:90%
It makes you purge.

00:33:17.000 --> 00:33:19.620 align:middle line:84%
We would, in our culture,
we would say vomit.

00:33:19.620 --> 00:33:22.020 align:middle line:84%
But they call it
purging, cleansing

00:33:22.020 --> 00:33:25.730 align:middle line:84%
your body of all the
ills, of the toxins.

00:33:25.730 --> 00:33:27.760 align:middle line:84%
And not the toxins
only that come

00:33:27.760 --> 00:33:29.230 align:middle line:84%
from our food but
the toxins that

00:33:29.230 --> 00:33:32.210 align:middle line:84%
come from the newspaper, that
come from television, that

00:33:32.210 --> 00:33:33.870 align:middle line:84%
come from our doubts
about ourselves.

00:33:33.870 --> 00:33:35.770 align:middle line:84%
And you actually
do-- most people--

00:33:35.770 --> 00:33:38.237 align:middle line:90%
purge quite dramatically.

00:33:38.237 --> 00:33:39.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Extensively.

00:33:39.070 --> 00:33:39.653 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yeah.

00:33:39.653 --> 00:33:41.820 align:middle line:84%
And it's not what
I would call fun.

00:33:41.820 --> 00:33:45.380 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes it goes
the other way also.

00:33:45.380 --> 00:33:48.190 align:middle line:84%
And not every single
person, but it's

00:33:48.190 --> 00:33:50.810 align:middle line:84%
almost like that's
part of what makes

00:33:50.810 --> 00:33:54.820 align:middle line:84%
it so humbling to
interact with the plant.

00:33:54.820 --> 00:33:57.070 align:middle line:84%
Because the plant,
then-- they call

00:33:57.070 --> 00:33:59.630 align:middle line:84%
her a mother-- she
does come to you.

00:33:59.630 --> 00:34:02.160 align:middle line:84%
And she-- you see
things, you can

00:34:02.160 --> 00:34:04.364 align:middle line:84%
see the-- it depends
on the person,

00:34:04.364 --> 00:34:06.030 align:middle line:84%
it's very, very
personal-- but sometimes

00:34:06.030 --> 00:34:07.920 align:middle line:84%
you can see the
veins and the blood

00:34:07.920 --> 00:34:09.840 align:middle line:84%
running through your
own hand or your body.

00:34:09.840 --> 00:34:11.670 align:middle line:84%
You can see inside
of a leaf, you

00:34:11.670 --> 00:34:15.460 align:middle line:84%
see patterns in the sky that
you didn't know were there,

00:34:15.460 --> 00:34:18.785 align:middle line:84%
you actually have
visions of animals

00:34:18.785 --> 00:34:20.409 align:middle line:84%
that you don't even
know what they are.

00:34:20.409 --> 00:34:23.070 align:middle line:84%
You'll see anacondas,
you might see jaguars,

00:34:23.070 --> 00:34:25.380 align:middle line:84%
you'll sometimes see
the face of a shaman.

00:34:25.380 --> 00:34:28.520 align:middle line:84%
It sounds very trippy
and dramatic, and it is,

00:34:28.520 --> 00:34:33.060 align:middle line:84%
but I just want to talk about
it with a real reverence.

00:34:33.060 --> 00:34:33.656 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:34:33.656 --> 00:34:35.239 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Because for
indigenous people

00:34:35.239 --> 00:34:37.120 align:middle line:84%
and doing it in the
rainforest with them--

00:34:37.120 --> 00:34:40.429 align:middle line:90%
which is a tremendous honor.

00:34:40.429 --> 00:34:42.440 align:middle line:84%
They've been doing this
for thousands of years

00:34:42.440 --> 00:34:43.889 align:middle line:84%
and this is where
they receive all

00:34:43.889 --> 00:34:46.900 align:middle line:84%
of their prophetic information,
all of their profound wisdom.

00:34:46.900 --> 00:34:49.199 align:middle line:84%
And these people,
although we would

00:34:49.199 --> 00:34:51.520 align:middle line:84%
call them primitive
in the way they live,

00:34:51.520 --> 00:34:54.060 align:middle line:84%
are highly, highly
sophisticated in ways

00:34:54.060 --> 00:34:55.419 align:middle line:90%
that we are quite primitive.

00:34:55.419 --> 00:34:57.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So they guide you
through the experience.

00:34:57.460 --> 00:34:57.830 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yes.

00:34:57.830 --> 00:35:00.230 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that's the way
that really should be done.

00:35:00.230 --> 00:35:02.270 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well, I can't
say should really.

00:35:02.270 --> 00:35:04.560 align:middle line:84%
I kind of try to avoid
that word when possible.

00:35:04.560 --> 00:35:08.790 align:middle line:84%
But I invite people to consider
the possibility, let's say,

00:35:08.790 --> 00:35:13.110 align:middle line:84%
that this is the most authentic
encounter with that teaching

00:35:13.110 --> 00:35:13.940 align:middle line:90%
plant.

00:35:13.940 --> 00:35:19.020 align:middle line:84%
And it's a central part of
the culture, of the teachings,

00:35:19.020 --> 00:35:21.580 align:middle line:84%
for many of the
indigenous tribes.

00:35:21.580 --> 00:35:25.120 align:middle line:84%
And we have received tremendous
benefit ourself from them.

00:35:25.120 --> 00:35:27.930 align:middle line:84%
And we realize that much of
it has come from the plant.

00:35:27.930 --> 00:35:29.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it allows
you to see the earth

00:35:29.930 --> 00:35:32.219 align:middle line:84%
as the mother would
see the earth?

00:35:32.219 --> 00:35:32.760 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: Yes.

00:35:32.760 --> 00:35:33.468 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In a way.

00:35:33.468 --> 00:35:35.020 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: You actually-- yes.

00:35:35.020 --> 00:35:35.520 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:35:35.520 --> 00:35:40.480 align:middle line:84%
And I'll just say, she is who's
speaking through that plant.

00:35:40.480 --> 00:35:43.330 align:middle line:84%
So you have a
direct relationship

00:35:43.330 --> 00:35:45.820 align:middle line:84%
with the being,
the Gaia-- here we

00:35:45.820 --> 00:35:48.540 align:middle line:84%
are at Gaiam-- the
actual Gaia spirit.

00:35:48.540 --> 00:35:49.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:35:49.740 --> 00:35:54.990 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: She and you become in
a kind of collaborative oneness.

00:35:54.990 --> 00:35:57.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I have heard that
is a life changing journey.

00:35:57.450 --> 00:35:59.680 align:middle line:84%
That you don't ever
go back once you

00:35:59.680 --> 00:36:02.590 align:middle line:84%
have that experience of
what you gain-- not gain,

00:36:02.590 --> 00:36:05.320 align:middle line:84%
but what you
experience and what you

00:36:05.320 --> 00:36:08.620 align:middle line:84%
learn changes who
you are for life.

00:36:08.620 --> 00:36:11.230 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well, it
changes-- yes, it does.

00:36:11.230 --> 00:36:14.727 align:middle line:84%
It almost reveals who you
are rather than changes it.

00:36:14.727 --> 00:36:15.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:36:15.560 --> 00:36:20.480 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: So I think the
real verb to use is reveals.

00:36:20.480 --> 00:36:24.200 align:middle line:84%
It unconceals who
you are to yourself.

00:36:24.200 --> 00:36:26.900 align:middle line:84%
And you start to realize
that you are an ecosystem.

00:36:26.900 --> 00:36:29.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I never thought
of myself as an ecosystem

00:36:29.330 --> 00:36:32.850 align:middle line:84%
until I had an experience
with the plant ayahuasca.

00:36:32.850 --> 00:36:34.790 align:middle line:84%
And now I know I
am an ecosystem.

00:36:34.790 --> 00:36:36.590 align:middle line:84%
It's not that I live
in an ecosystem,

00:36:36.590 --> 00:36:38.950 align:middle line:84%
and you take care of
all this stuff out here.

00:36:38.950 --> 00:36:42.530 align:middle line:84%
Yes, I am an ecosystem, I
am part of the ecosystem.

00:36:42.530 --> 00:36:43.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In what way?

00:36:43.770 --> 00:36:46.490 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: Well, I'm
a biological being.

00:36:46.490 --> 00:36:50.840 align:middle line:90%
I'm a spirit in biological form.

00:36:50.840 --> 00:36:55.270 align:middle line:84%
I take from the ecological
resources around me

00:36:55.270 --> 00:36:56.400 align:middle line:90%
and I give back to them.

00:36:56.400 --> 00:37:01.430 align:middle line:84%
And that puts you in right
relation with the communion

00:37:01.430 --> 00:37:04.170 align:middle line:90%
and the community of life.

00:37:04.170 --> 00:37:07.870 align:middle line:84%
Rather than being what Thomas
Berry, the great cosmologist,

00:37:07.870 --> 00:37:11.290 align:middle line:90%
calls our species.

00:37:11.290 --> 00:37:14.830 align:middle line:84%
He says that we've been
in species isolation

00:37:14.830 --> 00:37:17.700 align:middle line:84%
and that we're so isolated from
other species we don't even

00:37:17.700 --> 00:37:21.410 align:middle line:84%
realize we're part of the
community of life, we're here,

00:37:21.410 --> 00:37:24.620 align:middle line:84%
we think, to exploit and
use the community of life

00:37:24.620 --> 00:37:25.870 align:middle line:90%
for our own gain.

00:37:25.870 --> 00:37:29.630 align:middle line:84%
And that has us in a
real fix as a species.

00:37:29.630 --> 00:37:32.670 align:middle line:84%
We may not be forever
welcome on this planet

00:37:32.670 --> 00:37:33.960 align:middle line:90%
if we don't cut that out.

00:37:33.960 --> 00:37:34.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:37:34.580 --> 00:37:36.120 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: So the Earth's
going to be fine,

00:37:36.120 --> 00:37:37.650 align:middle line:84%
but are we going
to be allowed to--

00:37:37.650 --> 00:37:38.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: On it.

00:37:38.460 --> 00:37:39.410 align:middle line:90%
>>TWIST: --stay.

00:37:39.410 --> 00:37:41.060 align:middle line:84%
So I don't mean
to make us wrong.

00:37:41.060 --> 00:37:43.960 align:middle line:84%
That was-- indigenous
people would never do that.

00:37:43.960 --> 00:37:49.870 align:middle line:84%
But we've kind of lost our
relations and our relationship

00:37:49.870 --> 00:37:54.220 align:middle line:84%
with the very thing that
supports life and supports us.

00:37:54.220 --> 00:37:57.070 align:middle line:84%
And we're kind of
destroying our own nest.

00:37:57.070 --> 00:37:58.560 align:middle line:90%
And none of us want to do that.

00:37:58.560 --> 00:37:59.310 align:middle line:90%
There is nobody--

00:37:59.310 --> 00:37:59.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:37:59.630 --> 00:38:00.280 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: --who's
doing it on purpose.

00:38:00.280 --> 00:38:00.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Intentionally.

00:38:00.650 --> 00:38:01.150 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:38:01.150 --> 00:38:04.550 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: It's all based
in unconscious, unexamined

00:38:04.550 --> 00:38:06.850 align:middle line:84%
assumptions that we
don't even realize

00:38:06.850 --> 00:38:08.440 align:middle line:90%
we are doing damage with.

00:38:08.440 --> 00:38:10.910 align:middle line:84%
Just like I didn't
realize I was building

00:38:10.910 --> 00:38:13.267 align:middle line:90%
an island in the Pacific Ocean--

00:38:13.267 --> 00:38:13.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:38:13.850 --> 00:38:14.700 align:middle line:84%
>>TWIST: --with
my water bottles.

00:38:14.700 --> 00:38:15.366 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, yes.

00:38:15.366 --> 00:38:17.340 align:middle line:90%
And there's so much around that.

00:38:17.340 --> 00:38:19.670 align:middle line:84%
And I really encourage people
